      "repair_reason": "This draft needs contributor real-behavior proof and maintainer/security approval for the TLS interception design before an automated repair lane would be appropriate.; Needs attention: The diff introduces a local TLS MITM backend, and current-head key hardening still returns reusable signing keys when ACL repair fails.; Review finding: [P1] Preserve post-tool message streams — extensions/anthropic/interactive-proxy... (sha=515f5859d6ff35e5ffa614423fc466e2d5d53819)",
      "review_summary": "The PR adds an opt-in `claude-cli-interactive` Anthropic backend with a Bun loopback TLS proxy, Claude stream JSONL reconstruction, config inheritance, parser/reasoning bridge wiring, packaging/tests, and doctor warning changes.\n\nReproducibility: yes. for the review blockers: source inspection shows later `message_start` streams are suppressed, finalization only runs on `end_turn`, and key-hardening failures are ignored. I did not run a live Claude subscription or Telegram turn locally.",
